"title": "8426: evangelism, motivation for",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8426",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Evangelism arises from a natural response to the grace of God, a concern for those who have yet to hear the good news and a desire to be faithful to the great commission to bring the good news to the ends of the earth. Evangelism is guided and directed by the Holy Spirit.</p>\n<h2>Motives for evangelism</h2>\n<h3>Recognising God's call</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:11\">2TI 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:8-Isa6:9\">ISA 6:8–6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:1-Jonah1:2\">JON 1:1–1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:14-Acts22:15\">ACT 22:14–22:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:1\">2CO 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:7\">1TI 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>A divine compulsion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:16-1Cor9:17\">1CO 9:16–9:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:9\">JER 20:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:8\">AMO 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:20\">ACT 4:20</a></p>\n<h3>A God-given responsibility</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:17-Ezek3:20\">EZK 3:17–3:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:7-Ezek33:9\">EZK 33:7–33:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:10-1Cor3:15\">1CO 3:10–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:10-2Cor5:11\">2CO 5:10–5:11</a></p>\n<h3>A desire to win the lost</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:1\">ROM 10:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:19-1Cor9:23\">1CO 9:19–9:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:19-Acts20:20\">ACT 20:19–20:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:14-Rom1:15\">ROM 1:14–1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:1-Rom9:3\">ROM 9:1–9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:14\">ROM 11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:17-Rom15:20\">ROM 15:17–15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:20\">2CO 5:20</a></p>\n<h3>A recognition of coming judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:23\">JUD 1:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:20\">JAS 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:9\">2PE 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Responding to God's grace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:14-2Cor5:15\">2CO 5:14–5:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:18–5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:7\">EPH 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:12-1Tim1:16\">1TI 1:12–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Confidence in the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:16-Rom1:17\">ROM 1:16–1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:10-Isa55:11\">ISA 55:10–55:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:17-1Cor1:18\">1CO 1:17–1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:4-2Cor10:5\">2CO 10:4–10:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:8-2Tim1:9\">2TI 1:8–1:9</a></p>\n<h2>God directs and guides evangelism</h2>\n<h3>Divine guidance in evangelism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:26-Acts8:29\">ACT 8:26–8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:6-Acts16:10\">ACT 16:6–16:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:19-Acts5:20\">ACT 5:19–5:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:10-Acts9:11\">ACT 9:10–9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:19-Acts10:20\">ACT 10:19–10:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:12\">ACT 11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:2\">ACT 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:9-Acts18:11\">ACT 18:9–18:11</a></p>\n<h3>God opens the door for evangelism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:12\">2CO 2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:27\">ACT 14:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:9\">1CO 16:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:3\">COL 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:8\">REV 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Areas of ministry assigned by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:7-Gal2:9\">GAL 2:7–2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:15\">ACT 9:15</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit empowers evangelism</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:19-Matt10:20\">MAT 10:19–10:20</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:11\">MRK 13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:11-Luke12:12\">LUK 12:11–12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26-John15:27\">JHN 15:26–15:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:5\">1TH 1:5</a></p>\n<h2>Evangelism as a result of persecution</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:4-Acts8:5\">ACT 8:4–8:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:19-Acts11:21\">ACT 11:19–11:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:50-Acts13:51\">ACT 13:50–13:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:6-Acts14:7\">ACT 14:6–14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:2\">ACT 18:2</a></p>",
